For AW14, her Georgiana clutches, which were made from soft chalk goatskin, were emblazoned with washing detergents packaging and even a packet of Swan matches.

'This collection began with the idea of finding beauty in the banal,' said Anya.

'The vivid "pop" graphics of a washing powder box or the guilty pleasure of the humble chocolate digestive.

'I wanted to treat the everyday ordinary in an extraordinary way.'

